'''The Hangman's Noose''', also known as the "Omen Noose", is an uncommon phenomenon throughout the Backrooms. Those "selected" by this phenomenon will be the sole one to witness it, as well as being the only person to be affected by its anomalous properties.

This phenomenon is more likely to target people who possess one or more of the following traits:

* Lives alone.
* Has few relationships, romantic or otherwise.
* Is nonreligious.
* Was born in the Frontrooms.
* Suffers from any mental illness.
* Has a history of trauma or misfortune.
* Lacks any significant accomplishments.
* Had experienced a parent, a sibling's death, or a parental divorce before adulthood.
* Suffers from a severe addiction.


This phenomenon will only manifest when its victim is entirely alone. Upon manifestation, the victim will see a noose shrouded in darkness, usually located within the corner of a room. The wanderer will report being particularly drawn to the noose, with a psychological effect preventing them from looking away or leaving the area. Additionally, the victim will report feeling an overwhelming sense of dread and fear, often sending them into a panic attack.

After approximately thirty seconds, the victim will blink, causing the noose to vanish before their eyes.





















<center>
The Hangman's Noose will appear exactly one year before its victim commits suicide.







